╠══════════════════════════════════════╣
║         Chapter 1. Building          ║
╟──────────────────────────────────────╢
║ The Wheat Snooper builds on Windows, ║
║ Linux, and OS/2. To build it on any  ║
║ of the supported OSes, you need the  ║
║ Qt SDK, which you are able to        ║
║ download at:                         ║
║                                      ║
║   http://qt-project.org/             ║
║                                      ║
║ Then, when you're all set, make an   ║
║ empty directory for the build,       ║
║ change to it, and run one of the     ║
║ following commands:                  ║
║                                      ║
║   wheat/build-scripts/lin/build      ║
║                                      ║
║ for Winux,                           ║
║                                      ║
║   wheat/build-scripts/win/build      ║
║                                      ║
║ for Linux, and                       ║
║                                      ║
║   wheat/build-scripts/os2/build      ║
║                                      ║
║ for OS/2, where "wheat" is the       ║
║ directory of the source package.     ║
║                                      ║
║ Then the builded up TWS should       ║
║ appear in the current directory.     ║
║ Use "buildr" instead of "build" to   ║
║ build a release version and pack it  ║
║ into an installer.                   ║
║                                      ║
║ Please note, that even if it's       ║
║ tested only on Windows, Linux, and   ║
║ OS/2, The Wheat Snooper should       ║
║ properly build on any OS with        ║
║ an available Qt SDK of version,      ║
║ greater than 4.                      ║
║                                      ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════╝